http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Navakerala-March-from-January-15/article13982084.ece

The Navakerala March, a state-level campaign organised by the CPI(M) ahead of the Assembly elections this year, will commence from Kasaragod on January 15.Former party general secretary Prakash Karat is scheduled to inaugurate the march led by CPI(M) politburo member Pinarayi Vijayan. The inaugural function will be held at 4 p.m. at Uppala, Kasaragod. State secretary Kodiyeri Balakrishnan and Leader of the Opposition V.S. Achuthanandan will be among the leaders participating in the function. The march will highlight the slogan ‘secular, corruption-free, developing Kerala’.The month-long campaign will cover all Assembly constituencies before ending in a rally in Thiruvananthapuram on February 14. A pressnote issued by the State committee said CPI(M) leaders M.V. Govindan, K.J. Thomas, P.K. Sainaba, M.B. Rajesh, P.K. Biju, A. Sampath, and K.T. Jaleel will be part of the march.The district-wise schedule for the march is: Kasaragode January 15, 16; Kannur January 17, 18; Kozhikode January 20-22; Malappuram January 23-26; Palakad- January 27-29; Thrissur January 30-February 1; Ernakulam February 2-4; Idukki February 5; Kottayam February 6- 7; Alappuzha February 8-9; Pathanamthitta February 10; Kollam February 11-13 and Thiruvananthapuram February 14.